Package: xtop
Version: 0.42.0-1
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6
Recommends: postgresql, journalctl
Installed-Size: 23450
Maintainer: Farhan Tahir <farhan.003@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/ftahirops/xtop
Description: Incident-first root-cause analysis console for Linux
 v0.42.0 adds an opt-in ResourceGuard: when XTOP_GUARD=1, xtop monitors
 host load-avg, host busy%, and its own CPU consumption, and progressively
 sheds expensive collectors (log tailer, OTel traces, eBPF watchdog,
 deep-scan) on a busy host. Escalates after 3 sustained ticks, recovers
 after 10 clean ticks. Interval extends up to 2x base on severe load.
 Also fixes the web dashboard 401 (cookie-based auth) and the daemon
 mode's missing fleet push.
